     <section name="Description">

  <p>JCalendarButton is a simple java swing component that displays
a popup calendar next to a date input field.</p>

<p>
Here is a sample of what the buttons look like. To try this demo for yourself, <a href="http://www.donandann.com/bio">click here</a>.
Try pressing the language buttons at the bottom of the applet to see the buttons change automatically for different countries. 
<br></br><img src="images/bio.png" alt="Biorhythm screen"/>
<br/>Note: The source code for this cool sample application is in the <a href="source-repository.html">source repository</a> for this project.
</p>
<p>
If you are looking for an actual calendar component, try the <a href="../calendarpanel">Calendar Panel</a>.
The demo on the first page also shows several JCalendarButtons in use.
</p>

