      <subsection name="Maven Integration">
<p>
To include JCalendarButton in your <a href="http://maven.apache.org/">Maven</a> projects, just add the following dependency to your Maven project:
</p>
<p>
<code>
&lt;dependency&gt;<br/>
&#160;&#160;    	&lt;groupId&gt;${project.groupId}&lt;/groupId&gt;<br/>
&#160;&#160;    	&lt;artifactId&gt;${project.artifactId}&lt;/artifactId&gt;<br/>
&#160;&#160;    	&lt;version&gt;${project.version}&lt;/version&gt;<br/>
    &lt;/dependency&gt;<br/>
</code>
</p>

      </subsection>
      <subsection name="OSGi packaging">
<p>
JCalendarButton is already configured as an <a href="http://www.osgi.org">OSGi</a> bundle.
To use it in your OSGi project, just include JCalendarButton in the
manifest of the bundles that will be using JCalendarButton.
Remember to install the JCalendarButton jar in your OSGi environment.
</p>
<p>
<code>
OBR Repository index:<br/>
${project.organization.url}/${OBRRepositoryIndex}<br/>
Manifest import:<br/>
Import-Package: ${project.groupId};resolution:=optional;version=${project.version}
</code>
</p>

